  "text": "The Ponseti method is successful in children who present after the neonatal period. Bor, Herzenberg and Frick [CITATION_1] reviewed a number of children who were first seen after the age of three months in whom conservative treatment had failed. After a period of 24 months, only one of 36 feet (2.8%) required extensive surgery.",
